abstract: Cory Booker said that not making the December debate would force “difficult decisions” about his candidacy. Then a big rival dropped out.
snippet: Cory Booker said that not making the December debate would force “difficult decisions” about his candidacy. Then a big rival dropped out.
lead_paragraph: SOMEWHERE ON U.S. HWY 63, Iowa — Senator Cory Booker sat in the front seat of an S.U.V. grinning and clutching his iPhone 11 Pro as he quickly took stock of the past 36 hours in Iowa.

abstract: He cleared a final polling hurdle to join six other candidates, ensuring there won’t be an all-white debate.
snippet: He cleared a final polling hurdle to join six other candidates, ensuring there won’t be an all-white debate.
lead_paragraph: The entrepreneur Andrew Yang has qualified for next week’s Democratic debate, bringing the lineup to seven and ensuring that the candidates onstage will not all be white, though the lineup still does not include any black or Latino candidates.

abstract: She is taking on Pete Buttigieg directly, whacking at Mike Bloomberg and emphasizing her gender as the top woman left in the race.
snippet: She is taking on Pete Buttigieg directly, whacking at Mike Bloomberg and emphasizing her gender as the top woman left in the race.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Faced with questions about her viability in a general election and ceding ground to opponents in the primary, Senator Elizabeth Warren is abandoning her above-the-fray approach and delivering her most forceful and direct criticism yet of her Democratic opponents.

headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Seeks a Second Act After Slip From the Top
headline_print_headline: After Slipping in the Race, Warren Goes on the Offensive

lead_paragraph: Gail Collins: Bret, how do you feel about billionaires? Not personally — I’m sure some of your best friends are billionaires — but as presidential candidates. Ever since Michael Bloomberg started running, there’s been a lot of complaining about rich guys trying to buy the race. Does that worry you, or do you find people like Bloomberg and Tom Steyer to be, um, valuable additions?

abstract: Mr. Buttigieg will also open his fund-raisers to the press and identify people raising money for his campaign, in a significant concession from a candidate facing pressure over transparency.
snippet: Mr. Buttigieg will also open his fund-raisers to the press and identify people raising money for his campaign, in a significant concession from a candidate facing pressure over transparency.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mayor Pete Buttigieg will disclose his management consulting clients, open his fund-raisers to reporters and reveal the names of people raising money for his presidential campaign, his campaign announced Monday, a series of significant concessions toward transparency for a candidate under increasing pressure to release more details about his personal employment history and campaign finances.

abstract: After Kamala Harris’s departure from the presidential race, the people who saw their own paths reflected in hers are thinking about what comes next.
snippet: After Kamala Harris’s departure from the presidential race, the people who saw their own paths reflected in hers are thinking about what comes next.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The first black woman to be elected mayor of San Francisco, London Breed, considers Senator Kamala Harris something of a political soul mate. When Ms. Harris announced her White House bid in Oakland, Calif., in January, Ms. Breed was one of the 20,000 supporters there loudly celebrating, and she endorsed the campaign from the beginning.
